```
Ah, I see. There are *two* calls to `getShuffleCost`. I have been targeting the second one. The first one is `ShuffleVectorInst::getShuffleCost`. The second is `TTI.getShuffleCost`. The stack trace points to `VectorCombine::foldShuffleOfSelects`, which calls `TTI.getShuffleCost`. So I am targeting the right call.

Let's look at the scope again.
```cpp
// ...
  if (!isa<SelectInst>(V1) || !isa<SelectInst>(V2)) {
    if (isa<Constant>(V1) && isa<Constant>(V2))
