// ...
```
This `SrcVTy` is modified. It's not the original source type. This is why my attempt to use it failed.

The correct fix is indeed to use `cast<VectorType>(I.getOperand(0)->getType())` or `cast<VectorType>(V1->getType())`.

Given the persistent build errors, I will try one last time with the most robust `sed` command I can think of. I will use a different delimiter to avoid escaping issues and be very specific.

```bash
sed -i "s|OldCost += TTI.getShuffleCost(SK, DstVecTy, Mask, CostKind, 0, nullptr,|OldCost += TTI.getShuffleCost(SK, cast<VectorType>(V1->getType()), Mask, CostKind, 0, nullptr,|" llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VectorCombine.cpp
```
I'm using `V1->getType()` which is equivalent to `I.getOperand(0)->getType()` but shorter and was already defined in the function. This should work. If this fails with the same `SrcVTy` error, the environment is irrevocably broken.

```bash
